history.text: So, I am confused by the critics rating systems. Rotten Tomatoes doesn't make sense to me. How does a movie receive an 84% and a 6.9/10?
Right? It had no major point to it.
People are obsessed with this movie... but I've never understood why. An A-minus from CinemaScore? Really?
A self-help comedy, I don't think the Substance of the film mattered to anyone. It's move of a cult favorite, like the room. Terrible but people like it.
Yeah... I guess I will never understand that. I also didn't know that Tina Fey had written it. Is this her claim to fame before SNL?
She was a comedian and writer before the film
Do you usually watch fails of this genre?
Not really. I definitely prefer more action-style films. Lots of Superhero films
How about you?
I like all types of films, I enjoy superhero films recently I saw Black Panther. I think my taste in films change as I get older.
Did you enjoy Black Panther?
Yes, I was afraid it was going to be overrated but it was perfect.
I just finished the film last night myself and felt the same way, but also had the same result! I am thinking of going to see it again because it was that good!
What would you rate mean girls
It just wasn't memorable or exciting to me. Nothing across the board, whether it be the acting, costuming, cinematography, script, etc. Was any good to me
The only positives I can come up with is I do think the film was cast correctly.
How about you?
I think I would give it a 5/10. I think it means something to younger people but of course you become wiser and understand how this film has no heart behind it.
I will admit that there does seem to at least be a good message of avoiding being in a clique during grade school.
I guess you are right. The other message  being do not have compassion for people who do you wrong.
